The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Essar Steel quarterly profit soars

 Mumbai, July 27 (PTI): Essar Steel has reported a 300 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 207.71 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 50.44 crore for the same quarter in 2004.

 The companys total income from operations grew to Rs 1652.89 crore compared with Rs 1327.74 crore during the corresponding period of the previous year, Essar Steel said in a release here today.

 As a consequence of the acquisition of HY Grade Pellets Limited and Steel Corporation of Gujarat Limited, the total income of the consolidated entity after necessary adjustments stood at Rs 1655.78 crore and net profit was Rs 233.65 crore, the release said.

 Essar Steel managing director Prashant Ruia said the results have underscored the values attached to technology, customer satisfaction and international standards of quality. 

 This is especially true in the light of the current softening of steel prices, rising imports and firm raw material prices. Our plan or capacity enhancement and total integration is on course and will make the company retain its competitive edge in domestic and international markets, he added.

 The hot-rolled coil production by the company during the first quarter grew by over 16 per cent to 6.46 lakh tonnes against 5.59 lakh tonnes in the same period during previous fiscal, it said. 

 Videocon net 

 Videocon International today reported a 50.43 per cent rise in net profit of Rs 66.13 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 43.96 crore for the same quarter last year.

 Total income has increased to Rs 1,253.09 crore from Rs 975.08 crore in the year-ago period, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.




